# Linux Permissions & User Management

## Lab Overview

This lab explores Linux file permissions and user management concepts inside Kali Linux.
Understanding file ownership, permission structures, and user privileges is critical for both system administration and cybersecurity operations.

This lab demonstrates how users are created, how permissions are assigned to files, and how access control works within a Linux system.

---

## Lab Objectives

By completing this lab you will learn how to:

• Create new users
• Modify group membership
• Inspect file permissions
• Change file permissions with chmod
• Change file ownership with chown
• Understand numeric permission values (744, 600, etc)

